  <brief_title>Phase 2A Study of Setipiprant Tablets in Androgenetic Alopecia in Males</brief_title>
  <official_title>Multicenter, Randomized, Double-Blind, Placebo-Controlled, Phase 2A Study of Setipiprant Tablets in Androgenetic Alopecia in Males With a Comparator Arm</official_title>
  <sponsors>
    <lead_sponsor>
      <agency>Allergan</agency>
      <agency_class>Industry</agency_class>
    </lead_sponsor>
  </sponsors>
  <source>Allergan</source>
  <oversight_info>
    <has_dmc>No</has_dmc>
  </oversight_info>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      This study will evaluate the safety, tolerability and efficacy of the oral administration of
      setipiprant tablets 1000 mg twice daily (BID) relative to placebo and active comparator,
      finasteride 1 mg once daily, in 18 to 41 years old males with androgenetic alopecia (AGA).
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
